'''Mukul Dev''' is an [[India]]n television and film actor known for his [[Hindi film]]s and TV serials and music albums. He has also acted in few [[Tamil language|Tamil]] , [[Malayalam]], [[Kannada language|Kannada]] and [[Telugu cinema|Telugu films]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-21/news-interviews/29458871_1_hindi-film-mukul-dev-share-screen-space|title=Mukul Dev's dozen films in two years|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|first=Aparna|last=Phadke|accessdate=19 October 2011|date=21 April 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907173904/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-21/news-interviews/29458871_1_hindi-film-mukul-dev-share-screen-space|deadurl=no|archivedate=7 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> . He received the 7th Amrish Puri Award, for excellence in acting for his role in ''[[Yamla Pagla Deewana]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mukul-Dev-gets-Amrish-Puri-Award-for-Yamla-Pagla-Deewana/articleshow/9324363.cms|title=Mukul Dev gets Amrish Puri Award for Yamla Pagla Deewana|newspaper=The Times of India|first=Suruchi|last=Sharma|date=22 July 2011|accessdate=19 October 2011}}</ref>
He is also a trained pilot from the [[Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Uran Akademi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28377623_1_rahul-dev-mukul-dev-shooting|first=Diksha|last=Kamra|title=Mukul Dev is back in action|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=19 October 2011|date=18 January 2011|archivedate=7 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907174332/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28377623_1_rahul-dev-mukul-dev-shooting|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Career== Mukul Dev made his acting debut on TV through a serial ''Mumkin'' playing role of Vijay Pandey in 1996. He also acted in Doordarshan's [[Ek Se Badh Kar Ek]], a comedy Bollywood countdown show.
He got his break in films through ''[[Dastak (1996 film)|Dastak]]'' as ACP Rohit Malhotra in the same year which also introduced crowned [[Miss Universe]] [[Sushmita Sen]]. He appeared in several films such as ''[[Qila (film)|Qila]]'' (1998), ''[[Wajood (1998 film)|Wajood]]'' (1998), ''[[Kohram]]'' (1999) and ''[[Mujhe Meri Biwi Se Bachaao]]'' (2001). He acted in several television serials in the 2000s such as ''[[Kahin Diyaa Jale Kahin Jiyaa]]'' (2001), ''[[Kahaani Ghar Ghar Kii]]'' (2003), ''[[Pyar Zindagi Hai]]'' (2003) and in a dance competition show ''[[Kabhi Kabhii Pyaar Kabhi Kabhii Yaar]]'' (2008). In recent years he has played supporting roles in films like ''[[Yamla Pagla Deewana]]'' (2011), ''[[Son of Sardaar]]'' (2012), ''[[R... Rajkumar]]'' (2013) and ''[[Jai Ho (film)|Jai Ho]]'' (2014).
He was also the host of ''[[Fear Factor India]]'' of Season 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/mukul-dev-jat-buffalo-mission-070209721.html|title=Mukul Dev - the 'Jat' on a buffalo mission!|work=[[Yahoo! News]]|date=16 September 2011|accessdate=19 October 2011|archivedate=19 May 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120519123520/http://in.news.yahoo.com/mukul-dev-jat-buffalo-mission-070209721.html|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
